                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/797: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-31T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 31 [<hi rend="italic">30</hi>], 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 30—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1152. Following from American Consul General at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 29, 8 p.m. Government Mandate has been issued December 29th
                            postponing the date of going into effect of the law of May 4, 1931,
                            relating to jurisdiction over foreigners in China. When I have confirmed
                            the text I will telegraph translation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
